### Producer Staff Invite — VSCode REST Client (regression)
### Base: http://localhost:3000/api/v1/producer
### Auth: Replace {{token}} with a valid producer JWT or use cookie from browser after login.

@base = http://localhost:3000/api/v1/producer
@token = YOUR_PRODUCER_TOKEN_HERE

### 1) Email only (role string) — expect 201 or 401 if no token
POST {{base}}/staff/invite
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "email": "someone@example.com",
  "role": "STAFF"
}

### 2) Phone only — expect 201 or 401
POST {{base}}/staff/invite
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "phone": "+8801XXXXXXXXX",
  "role": "STAFF"
}

### 3) Both email and phone — expect 201 or 401
POST {{base}}/staff/invite
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "email": "someone@example.com",
  "phone": "+8801XXXXXXXXX",
  "roleKey": "PRODUCER_VIEWER"
}

### 4) Invalid: missing email and phone — expect 400 VALIDATION_ERROR
POST {{base}}/staff/invite
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "roleKey": "PRODUCER_VIEWER"
}

### 5) Invalid: bad role — expect 400 INVALID_ROLE
POST {{base}}/staff/invite
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "email": "a@b.com",
  "roleKey": "INVALID_ROLE"
}

### 6) No auth — expect 401 (omit Authorization header)
POST {{base}}/staff/invite
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "someone@example.com",
  "role": "VIEWER"
}
